history.content:
I had this exact same problem this semester, and the CalCentral people told me that dropping and readding either class involved in the swap would cancel it.

Unfortunately, that seems to be bugged.  I dropped and readded the class that was scheduled to be switched out, but still got dropped from it when I got off the waitlist for the other class.  So unless they've fixed this issue by now (which they probably haven't), dropping and readding 61B probably won't help you.  Your best bet would most likely be to either drop and readd the UGBA class (I don't know for sure if that would cancel the swap, but it would seem very strange if it didn't) or just wait for the swap to succeed, then add 61B again (assuming there are still open seats).

For the next semester, the classes that I ideally want to take is UGBA 103, CS 61B, EE 16B, Data 100. During the initial registration, I signed up for 61B, 16B, Data 100. Then, I realized that I should go ahead and put myself on the waitlist of UGBA 103, so I initiated a swap. Now in Phase 2, I just want to keep all the classes I am registered, and on the waitlist for. I am not sure how to do this, and if I would have to cancel the swap, but my priority is to keep my current spot on the UGBA waitlist. What would you suggest? Is there anyway I can keep my positions and just cancel the swap since its phase 2?  I am EECS so I would not mind dropping 61B and resigning up now, but I am not sure if that will keep me on the waitlist based on the swap form. In addition, It does not let me sign up for more units, so while I am technically on the waitlist for 16, when the swap occurs or fails, I will only be in 12.
history.subject: Cal Central Issues/ Advice
